# Google OAuth Configuration
# Get your Client ID from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
# 
# ============================================================================
# STEP-BY-STEP GUIDE TO OBTAIN GOOGLE OAUTH CLIENT ID
# ============================================================================
#
# 1. CREATE OR SELECT A GOOGLE CLOUD PROJECT
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Click "Select a project" at the top
#    - Click "New Project" or select an existing one
#
# 2. ENABLE REQUIRED APIs
#    - In the left sidebar, go to "APIs & Services" > "Library"
#    - Search for and enable these APIs:
#      * YouTube Data API v3
#      * Google+ API (for user profile information)
#
# 3. CREATE OAUTH 2.0 CREDENTIALS
#    - Go to "APIs & Services" > "Credentials"
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "OAuth client ID"
#    - If prompted, configure the OAuth consent screen first:
#      * Choose "External" user type
#      * Fill in app name, user support email, and developer contact
#      * Add scopes: youtube.upload, youtube, userinfo.email, userinfo.profile
#      * Add test users if in testing mode
#
# 4. CONFIGURE WEB APPLICATION
#    - Application type: "Web application"
#    - Name: "Beast Clipping" (or your preferred name)
#    
# 5. ADD AUTHORIZED REDIRECT URIs
#    Add these exact URIs (replace with your actual domains):
#    
#    For local development:
#    http://localhost:3000/oauth/callback
#    
#    For production (replace with your actual domain):
#    https://your-production-domain.com/oauth/callback
#    https://your-canister-id.ic0.app/oauth/callback
#    
#    ⚠️  IMPORTANT: The redirect URI must match EXACTLY (including http/https)
#
# 6. COPY YOUR CLIENT ID
#    - After creating, you'll see your Client ID
#    - Copy the entire Client ID (it looks like: xxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com)
#    - Paste it below, replacing "your_google_client_id_here"
#
# 7. CREATE YOUR .env FILE
#    - Copy this file to ".env" (without .example)
#    - Replace the placeholder value below with your actual Client ID
#    - Restart your development server after making changes
#
# ============================================================================

VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id_here

# Example of what a real Client ID looks like:
# VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=123456789012-abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz123456.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ============================================================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================================================
#
# If you see "Google Client ID not configured":
# - Make sure you created a .env file (not .env.example)
# - Verify the Client ID is correctly pasted
# - Restart your development server (npm run start or pnpm start)
#
# If OAuth fails with "redirect_uri_mismatch":
# - Check that the redirect URI in Google Cloud Console matches exactly
# - Make sure you're using the correct protocol (http vs https)
# - Verify the port number matches (e.g., :3000)
#
# If you see "access_denied":
# - The user cancelled the authorization
# - Try connecting again
#
# ============================================================================
